{"article_id":"HTEkZpFhcgV46i0x","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The United Kingdom ' s Supreme Court has ruled","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"that Boris Johnson ' s five-week suspension of Parliament was unlawful ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"further roiling British politics a month ahead of the Brexit deadline .","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"In a unanimous decision by 11 justices , the UK ' s highest court effectively ruled","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"that Johnson acted illegally","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"when he asked the Queen to prorogue Parliament for five weeks , from early September to October 14 .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"Johnson had argued","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"that he needed to end one parliamentary session","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"to get his agenda in order for the next ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"but the extraordinarily long break","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"- five full weeks -","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"angered critics and opposition members of Parliament ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"who saw Johnson as trying to sideline Parliament","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"so he could push through his vision of Brexit at all costs .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"The Court agreed ,","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"that prorogation itself isn ' t illegal ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"but that Johnson ' s maneuver was .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"\" The Court is bound to conclude , therefore ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"that the decision","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"to advise Her Majesty to prorogue Parliament","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"was unlawful","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"because it had the effect","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"of frustrating or preventing the ability of Parliament","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"to carry out its constitutional functions","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"without reasonable justification , \"","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"the justices wrote .","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"The UK ' s Supreme Court made a ruling","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"after court challenges to Johnson ' s prorogation had been filed in separate UK legal jurisdictions :","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"England and Wales , Northern Ireland , and Scotland .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"The English and Northern Irish courts dismissed the court cases ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"but the highest court in Scotland ruled","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"that Johnson ' s suspension was illegal .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"The discrepancies among the three forced the UK ' s highest court to weigh in ,","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"which it did last week in three days of televised hearings .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"The UK doesn ' t have a formal constitution ,","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"but the court ' s decision","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"to intercede on a political matter like prorogation","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"is a big deal ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"and it has the potential","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"to reshape the relationship between Parliament , the executive , and the courts moving forward .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Then there are the political implications ,","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"which are only starting to reveal themselves .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"This deals another brutal blow to Johnson ,","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"who ' s had a rough go of it in his two-month premiership .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"while many members of Parliament are likely celebrating ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"the UK ' s Supreme Court was pretty clear on what this decision doesn ' t do :","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"solve Brexit by the impending deadline of October 31 .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"\" It is important to emphasize that these cases are not about when or on what terms the United Kingdom is to leave the European Union , \"","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"the court wrote .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"The UK Supreme Court said","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"that","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"since Johnson ' s decision was unlawful ,","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"it was \" thus void and of no effect. \"","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"That basically means Parliament isn ' t suspended right now .","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"The justices said","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"\" it is for Parliament , and in particular the Speaker and the Lord Speaker to decide what to do next . \"","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"\" Unless there is some Parliamentary rule","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"of which we are unaware , \"","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"the justices added ,","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"\" they can take immediate steps","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"to enable each House to meet as soon as possible . \"","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"That means John Bercow , the current speaker of the House of Commons , can act pretty quickly .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"And he already has ,","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"saying","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"that Parliament will meet Wednesday , at 11:30 am .","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"Bercow said","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"Parliament would not host Prime Minister ' s Questions","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"( where Johnson answers questions from MPs )","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"because of the short notice .","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"And Johnson also just happens to be in New York City .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"And","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"even though Johnson is at the United Nations ,","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"it ' s going to be hard to ignore the chorus of opposition MPs","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"calling for his immediate resignation .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"The UK ' s highest court ruled","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"that the prime minister misled the monarch ,","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"and tried to circumvent and undercut lawmakers .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"This is stunning ,","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"and would normally take down any prime minister .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"But","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"as the Times columnist Alex Massie pointed out ,","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"\" In ordinary circumstances","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"I suspect","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"a prime minister would be expected to resign in the light of a ruling such as this .","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"But then ,","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"as the court has made clear ,","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"these are not ordinary circumstances . \"","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"Johnson told Sky News Tuesday","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"that he \" strongly disagrees \" with the Court ,","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"but he will respect the verdict .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"He ' s expected to leave the United Nations General Assembly a bit early","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"to return to 10 Downing Street","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"to deal with the fallout .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"Either way , it ' s clear that Johnson ' s power grab backfired , and badly .","depth":5},{"id":96,"text":"Johnson has staked his premiership on the promise","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"that he will deliver Brexit , \" do or die. \"","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"That means taking the United Kingdom out of the European Union with or without a deal on October 31 .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"The only deal on offer is still the one","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"that former Prime Minister Theresa May negotiated with the EU last year .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"Johnson and the EU remain at odds on the question of the Irish border ,","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"and the relationship between the EU and the UK has appeared even more publicly tense and frayed in recent weeks .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"Parliament has repeatedly rejected May ' s deal ,","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"but it also opposes leaving","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"without an agreement on October 31 .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"Johnson has insisted","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"that a disruptive , \" no-deal \" Brexit remain on the table as a threat","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"to get the EU to budge on a new deal .","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"But Parliament doesn ' t want to flirt with that prospect ,","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"and so has repeatedly tried to block a no-deal exit .","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"Johnson ' s suspension was an attempt","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"to basically take Parliament out of the equation ,","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"so he could do what he wanted .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"But Johnson ' s move","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"- to try to frustrate Parliament -","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"has proved to be an extraordinarily flawed one .","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"It focused Parliament ,","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"and united an opposition","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"that might not have otherwise existed .","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"He lost his majority in Parliament .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"Lawmakers still went ahead","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"and passed a law","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"trying to force Johnson to ask for a Brexit extension .","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"And Johnson ' s attempts","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"to get rid of the current Parliament","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"by calling for new elections","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"have also failed ,","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"as MPs won ' t go along with that plan right now .","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"Now Parliament may have even more opportunities","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"to exert its influence in the coming days .","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"But more time doesn ' t necessarily mean much","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"when it comes to the politics of Brexit -","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"and how the UK should leave the EU is as unresolved as ever .","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"How do you remove an egg from an omelette ?","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"Some say","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"that ' s how hard it is to remove the UK from the EU .","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"Meanwhile , Boris Johnson ' s Brexit strategy ended up in the United Kingdom ' s highest court .","depth":6},{"id":138,"text":"Looking for a quick way","depth":3},{"id":139,"text":"to keep up with the never-ending news cycle ?","depth":3},{"id":140,"text":"Host Sean Rameswaram will guide you through the most important stories at the end of each day .","depth":3},{"id":141,"text":"Subscribe on Apple Podcasts , Spotify , Overcast , or wherever you listen to podcasts .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":283,"left":279,"right":282,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":279,"left":176,"right":278,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":144,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":0,"right":143,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":143,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":154,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":146,"right":153,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":3,"right":145,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":145,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":148,"right":152,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":148,"left":6,"right":147,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":147,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":150,"right":151,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":149,"right":11,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":157,"right":173,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"